) some fated blow Come armed with power to lay my Arthur low , Fate would be kind to guide me to my rest , My dearest home , my soldier's faithful breast , To clasp his fainting form , close his dead eye , Bless his loved name , and breathe my latest sigh : Never even in death my Arthur I'll resign , Be all his sufferings , all his sorrows mine
